                <h2><u>Sensitivity Requirement</u></h2>
                <p> Class A prescription balances are designed for weighing of pharmaceutical substances required in filling of prescription. 
                A class A balance must have a <b>Sensitivity Requirement (SR)</b> of 6 mg or less. 
                SR is defined as the minimum weight that causes the pointer to move by one division.
                </p>
