                    <p><span><b>Solved Problem: </b></span> Calculate the SR of a prescription balance if a 20 mg weight on this balance was able to move the pointer by 2 divisions. Does this satisfy the SR for a Class A balance?</p>
                    <p><span><b>Approach: </b></span> SR is the amount of weight that can move the pointer by 1 division.</p>
                <div class="formulae"><p>$${20mg \over 2 \ divisions} = {x \over 1 \ division}$$</p></div>
